{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Lower sponsorship costs and requirements for skilled immigrant workers in the UK",
        "additional_details": "Increase the maximum age for meeting the lower salary threshold from 26 to 30\r\n\r\nIn 2024, the UK raised skilled worker Visa salary thresholds to \u00a330,960 for people under 26 and \u00a338,700 for people over 26, which we think prices many immigrants out of entry-level roles regardless of skill.\r\n \r\nMany employers must now pay \u00a31,500+ annually to sponsor non-UK staff. We think these costs and restrictions make hiring diverse global talent difficult, forcing thousands of skilled workers out, not due to lack of merit, but due to unrealistic, exclusionary policies.",
        "background": "Lower the salary threshold for all industries to the previous rate of \u00a326,200.\r\n \r\nLower the fee for Certificate of Sponsor (CoS) to the previous fee of \u00a3239\r\n \r\nLower the Immigration Skills Charge (ISC) to the previous fee of \u00a31,000 per year for large sponsors and \u00a3364 per year for small sponsors",
